This paper is primarily focused on the intersection of privacy and accuracy in data analysis, which falls under the category of "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the implementation of a programming framework for differential privacy, which involves database management (cs.DB), machine learning (cs.LG), and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the use of statistical techniques for accuracy estimation, which falls under the category of "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS).
